The only reason I would stay here again is that the manager kept in email contact with me (I preferred email -- he offered to call instead) regarding our room and was quite helpful.	In all fairness, the City Club Hotel was, at one time, my favorite place to stay in the city.	I would have preferred to stay elsewhere.	I'm a pretty tough critic of hotels, but I would stay at the City Club again.	The room, however, was so small and the bed so uncomfortable, that next time, rather than take the chance of this type of error happening again, I'd probably stay at the sort of big hotel I was trying to avoid in the first place.